{"updated_at": "2011-12-28T16:28:13Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-12-28T16:28:13Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3292359", "id": 3292359, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4218", "issue_id": 4218, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/bogdan", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F926d19e70f74c20f796d376aafa3c6e2.png", "id": 122436, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/events{/privacy}", "login": "bogdan", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/followers"}, "body": "No, it's not.\r\n\r\nWell in order to understand we should probably distinguish runner method from runner cache method.\r\n`__define_runner` defines the runner method.\r\n `__callback_runner_name` - builds the runner cache method name. This method is defined on the first run of runner method.\r\n\r\n`__reset_runner` undefines runner cache and don't touch the runner itself - and that is what we need when doing `set_callback` or `reset_callbacks`.\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "523829c6bd3543c15100f0a0"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4218#issuecomment-3292359"}
